commitResults.messageBody:
Session was using LocalDateTime to implement compareTo

This however, was buggy since for eg. Wed 08:00 compareTo Sat 08:00 may result in Wed being bigger which is not what we want.

This is due to Wed for example being assigned a Date field that is greater than the Date field assigned to Sat when using the defaulting in Session implementation.

Fixed this by refactoring compareTo to use own logic.

commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, there was an issue where the effects from one test case
would bleed over to the next as the Persons in TypicalPersons
were modified, causing the next tests to fail (particularly
toModelType_typicalPersonsFile_success). This is now fixed by
making TypicalPersons make copies of the original Persons every time
getTypicalAddressBook is called.
